
Ventrilo (or Vent for short) is a proprietary VoIP software that includes text chat.
The Ventrilo client and server are both available as freeware for use with up to 8 people on the same server (rented servers can maintain as many as 100+ people).So How many users can I have? (Ventrilo Tech Support) The server software is available for Microsoft Windows, Mac OS X, or Unix variants such as Linux, Kopi, Solaris, NetBSD and FreeBSD. The client is available for Windows and Mac OS X.http://www.ventrilo.com/download.php Presently[tpl]as of?|date=June 2012[/tpl], however, the Mac OS X client is still unable to properly use most servers, due to a lack of support for the widely used GSM codec.[tpl]Citation needed|reason=out of date? See Talk page: added in 2007?|date=January 2010[/tpl] A Linux version is planned,http://www.ventrilo.com/ but Mangler, a third-party Linux client, is available under the GPL license.http://gentoo-portage.com/media-sound/mangler/Dep There is also Ventrilode, a third-party client for the iPhone and iPod Touch.[tpl]cite web |title=Daily Apps: Aiko Island: Holidays, Ventrilode, Hex Empire, Aztec The Three Sun Pyramid Game, System Monitor with Battery Max |author=Leanna Lofte |date=13 December 2011 |url=http://www.tipb.com/2011/12/13/daily-apps-5/[/tpl]
Ventrilo currently supports GSM Full Rate and Speex as their main codecs.

==Usage==

Ventrilo is widely used by gamers who use the software to communicate with other players on the same team of a multiplayer game. Ventrilo is chosen by gamers because the client uses minimal CPU resources.[ref]Clas Olson, "The Tactical Importance of Voice Communication in
Massively Multiplayer Online Role-Playing Games", research paper at stylized-lotus.com http://stylized-lotus.com/Stylized_Lotus/Games_files/Paper.pdf, accessed 20 September 2010[/ref]
Ventrilo is also used as a call-in method on radio shows, and for general voice-chat.[tpl]Citation needed|date=September 2010[/tpl]

